    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Two Parties, for Better or Worse</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bernice Sisson letter disputes Bruce Bartlett's August 22 Op-Ed article on campaign promises of Vice Pres Al Gore</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Cost of Keeping Gore's Promises,'' by Bruce Bartlett (Op-Ed, Aug. 22):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Cost of Keeping Gore's Promises,'' by Bruce Bartlett (Op-Ed, Aug. 22):</p>
        <p>Now that we have read about the cost of keeping Al Gore's promises, can we read about the cost of not keeping them?</p>
        <p>Is education more expensive than prisons? Is a healthy population more a drain on the budget than an unhealthy one? And what is the human cost of neglect?</p>
        <p>BERNICE SISSON  Swarthmore, Pa., Aug. 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
